Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing people's argumentation using natural language processing techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper experiments with several machine learning methods to identify argument components. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing Web data and creating a gold standard corpus. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper experiments with machine learning methods. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing user-generated Web discourse, which has social implications.
